http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/All-set-for-Thiruvabharanam-procession/article13996276.ece

The customary ceremonial procession carrying the sacred jewellery, Thiruvabharanam, for the Makaravilakku festival at the Sabarimala Ayyappa Temple will set off from Pandalam on Wednesday afternoon.Unlike in the previous years, the boxes carrying the Thiruvabharanam will be kept at the Puthenmeda of the Valiyakoickal Palace as the Valiyakoickal Sastha Temple as well as the palace strongroom remain closed from Friday following the death of a senior member of the royal family a few days ago.The customary handing over of the ceremonial sword to the royal representative too will not be there as the palace is not in a position to send its representative to Sabarimala owing to the death of the family member.To be handed over to TDBAccording to Pandalam Palace managing committee president P.G. Sasikumar Varma, the Thiruvabharanam will be handed over to the Travancore Devaswom Board (TDB) officials on Wednesday morning and the three boxes carrying the sacred attire and allied jewellery will be kept at the Puthenmeda.The procession carrying the Thiruvabharanam will set off from the Puthenmeda at 1 p.m. on Wednesday.